      "writtenOn": "2017-08-29T23:55:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "do we want to have a standard set of basic recommendations so we don\u0027t end up with one service having GET/PUT and another one having READ/WRITE, and another one OBSERVE/INPUT? Maybe even an enumeration of \u0027basic\u0027 actions with detailed \"use this when ___\" descriptions, and then a \u0027special_action\u0027 field which is freeform text? Then we can (via codereview) recommend the use of common actions when appropriate.\n\nAt the very least I think we should have some basic list of spellings:\n  * READ\n  * WRITE\n  * ALTER\n  * DELETE\n  * INFO\n\netc.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 39,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "64990e5afcb95777fba8c818759c3a59f519de8f",
